                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Make moms breastfeed, says Gisele
                              Bundchen: Forceful                            
	Aug. 2: The Brazilian supermodel, Gisele Bundchen, has said that mothers should be forced to breastfeed for the first six months of a babys life.        
	The catwalk star, who lives in the US, said there should be a law preventing mothers from using formula milk. The 30-year-old told Harpers Bazaar magazine: I think breastfeeding really helped (me keep my figure).        
	Some people here (in the US) think they dont have to breastfeed, and I think Are you going to give chemical food to your child when they are so little?                            THE DAILY TELEGRAPH                                                                                                                                                  
